202
00:17:30,256 --> 00:17:32,193
I think you owe me an explanation.

203
00:17:36,111 --> 00:17:38,281
TO LEE ANNA

204
00:18:02,056 --> 00:18:04,150
The name Lee Anna is suspicious.

205
00:18:04,233 --> 00:18:05,211
Also, the Alumni Association?

206
00:18:06,291 --> 00:18:07,649
Hey.

207
00:18:07,732 --> 00:18:11,319
I called the number here
because I was curious about Lee Anna,

208
00:18:12,909 --> 00:18:14,233
and they told me right away.

209
00:18:26,622 --> 00:18:29,552
I had my reasons.

210
00:18:33,028 --> 00:18:35,640
I don't want to know.

211
00:18:35,723 --> 00:18:37,936
There's no reason that can make it okay

212
00:18:38,019 --> 00:18:39,738
for someone like you
to teach at a university.

213
00:18:39,821 --> 00:18:42,517
I mean, do people buy this?

214
00:18:43,581 --> 00:18:44,662
Seriously?

215
00:18:48,501 --> 00:18:51,736
I didn't do it intentionally.

216
00:19:06,926 --> 00:19:08,064
Professor Lee.

217
00:19:10,164 --> 00:19:12,504
If doing things unintentionally
makes it okay,

218
00:19:12,587 --> 00:19:14,333
why do you think we have laws?

219
00:19:16,066 --> 00:19:17,566
This is fraud.

220
00:19:21,515 --> 00:19:22,614
What should we do?

221
00:19:25,094 --> 00:19:25,981
Well?

222
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:30,689
Lee Anna.

223
00:19:32,405 --> 00:19:33,655
What should we do now?

224
00:19:59,424 --> 00:20:00,523
I'll stop.

225
00:20:02,495 --> 00:20:04,330
Please give me some time.

226
00:20:06,950 --> 00:20:08,651
How is it so easy for you?

227
00:20:12,198 --> 00:20:14,057
How can it become like it never happened?

228
00:20:15,712 --> 00:20:17,998
You stole someone else's life,

229
00:20:20,244 --> 00:20:21,836
so you must pay for it.

230
00:20:23,332 --> 00:20:24,400
Don't you think so?

231
00:20:27,085 --> 00:20:28,848
Nice.

232
00:20:30,763 --> 00:20:36,152
You have overwhelming support
from the young and the established,

233
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:39,376
while your wife is especially popular

234
00:20:39,459 --> 00:20:42,123
among the marginalized groups.

235
00:20:43,629 --> 00:20:45,455
I'm lucky.

236
00:20:46,701 --> 00:20:49,519
It's true she's playing an important role.

237
00:20:49,602 --> 00:20:50,929
So what you do want to do?

238
00:20:52,257 --> 00:20:56,565
What do you think about having her
run a school?

239
00:20:59,561 --> 00:21:01,463
The chairman of Dongsung University
is regretting

240
00:21:01,546 --> 00:21:03,063
after buying the school.

241
00:21:03,146 --> 00:21:05,487
The professors don't listen

242
00:21:06,263 --> 00:21:10,941
and the students are always complaining
and stirring up noise.

243
00:21:11,024 --> 00:21:12,402
He says it's a headache.

244
00:21:12,485 --> 00:21:14,308
Or perhaps

245
00:21:14,391 --> 00:21:18,110
a scholarship foundation geared towards
public interest might be good.

246
00:21:19,403 --> 00:21:22,247
It doesn't cost much,

247
00:21:22,330 --> 00:21:24,580
and it's quite effective.

248
00:21:25,188 --> 00:21:26,286
A scholarship foundation?

249
00:21:27,084 --> 00:21:29,510
It would be much better than

250
00:21:29,593 --> 00:21:32,725
having her stand at a subway station
with your campaign jacket on.

251
00:21:34,371 --> 00:21:36,760
-It's different.
-Yes, it's different.

252
00:21:47,431 --> 00:21:49,102
By next month,

253
00:21:52,260 --> 00:21:53,193
bring me three billion won.

254
00:21:56,006 --> 00:22:00,121
What is it?
Do you prefer criminal punishment?

255
00:22:01,487 --> 00:22:04,806
You didn't think
it would be so expensive, right?

256
00:22:07,301 --> 00:22:10,511
That's how it is with degrees.
They're expensive.

257
00:22:18,484 --> 00:22:21,745
You should demand what's possible.

258
00:22:24,612 --> 00:22:26,172
I don't have anything.

259
00:22:28,227 --> 00:22:29,989
That's not my problem.

260
00:22:31,011 --> 00:22:33,187
That's your problem.

261
00:22:33,270 --> 00:22:36,802
It's your problem for stealing my life.

262
00:22:38,258 --> 00:22:40,572
Don't reflect on yourself in front of
a judge who has nothing to do with me.

263
00:22:40,655 --> 00:22:42,130
Pay me back with money instead.

264
00:22:45,369 --> 00:22:49,041
Does your husband know this about you?

265
00:23:02,671 --> 00:23:04,413
You're really something.

266
00:23:05,964 --> 00:23:09,215
Hey. You should keep on using the stairs.

267
00:23:14,861 --> 00:23:16,592
