343
00:28:44,038 --> 00:28:48,987
How could you blow off this building?

344
00:28:49,648 --> 00:28:51,910
What's wrong with you?

345
00:28:52,343 --> 00:28:53,908
I'll take care of it.

346
00:28:54,482 --> 00:28:56,723
Take care of what?

347
00:28:59,746 --> 00:29:02,113
I'll just pay back the three billion won.

348
00:29:02,196 --> 00:29:03,804
It's nothing.

349
00:29:03,887 --> 00:29:04,857
What?

350
00:29:08,364 --> 00:29:10,204
I said I'll take care of it.

351
00:29:11,032 --> 00:29:12,951
Please stop it!

352
00:29:14,340 --> 00:29:18,503
You only know how to spend money.
You've never earned a cent in your life.

353
00:29:20,269 --> 00:29:22,963
How can you take care of anything?

354
00:29:24,631 --> 00:29:26,786
Tell me!

355
00:29:32,015 --> 00:29:33,685
I'm sorry,
it's because it's my first time.

356
00:29:33,768 --> 00:29:35,872
Yes, it's your first time.
Just press this.

357
00:29:38,551 --> 00:29:39,467
Okay?

358
00:29:40,168 --> 00:29:43,539
I'm leaving.
Don't forget the gathering this evening.

359
00:29:44,086 --> 00:29:46,239
From now on, Yu-mi will remind you.

360
00:29:55,940 --> 00:29:58,887
Hello, Professor Lee.
My name is Cho Yu-mi.

361
00:29:59,351 --> 00:30:03,621
Even the way we breathe has meaning
and we can get evaluated on it.

362
00:30:03,704 --> 00:30:05,164
You didn't think
it would be so expensive, right?

363
00:30:05,809 --> 00:30:08,876
That's how it is with degrees.
They're expensive.

364
00:30:20,161 --> 00:30:21,042
Hey.

365
00:30:27,617 --> 00:30:28,676
What brought you here?

366
00:30:30,248 --> 00:30:34,582
Our company is planning a small exhibition
and the person who was on the project

367
00:30:34,665 --> 00:30:37,574
ended up giving birth
earlier than she thought.

368
00:30:37,657 --> 00:30:39,165
We need some help.

369
00:30:40,090 --> 00:30:41,043
I see.

370
00:30:42,692 --> 00:30:45,712
Joseon literati paintings.
It's your specialty.

371
00:30:45,795 --> 00:30:47,017
Do you want to take over?

372
00:30:49,347 --> 00:30:51,135
Why don't you do it yourself?

373
00:30:51,932 --> 00:30:54,544
It's too small for me to do.

374
00:30:55,545 --> 00:30:58,246
The people who own these works
want to sell the paintings,

375
00:30:58,329 --> 00:31:00,254
but you know these kinds of works
don't increase in prices.

376
00:31:00,337 --> 00:31:02,667
The exhibition will be held
so we can promote the pieces.

377
00:31:04,617 --> 00:31:05,749
I don't know.

378
00:31:11,377 --> 00:31:14,754
There's no pressure
since it's not about making money.

379
00:31:18,170 --> 00:31:20,739
There's enough time to prepare it too.

380
00:31:23,921 --> 00:31:26,522
What is it? Is it too lame?

381
00:31:29,167 --> 00:31:31,685
I used to take jobs
like this at first too.

382
00:31:33,560 --> 00:31:37,038
No, it's not that...

383
00:31:38,027 --> 00:31:40,490
Can't you help me out this once?

384
00:31:43,397 --> 00:31:44,861
How much

385
00:31:46,836 --> 00:31:48,120
will they pay me?

386
00:31:49,373 --> 00:31:52,819
Come on, you know this won't pay much.

387
00:31:52,902 --> 00:31:55,410
It's not like you're looking for money.

388
00:31:57,368 --> 00:31:59,473
Please do it for me.

389
00:32:00,809 --> 00:32:03,027
Democratic Republican Party's Choi Ji-hoon

390
00:32:03,110 --> 00:32:05,124
is making prominent progress,

391
00:32:05,207 --> 00:32:07,837
but as factions of
the 51 newly-elected members

392
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:11,300
out of the 117
in the National Assembly are unclear,

393
00:32:11,383 --> 00:32:14,133
it's hard to predict the result.

394
00:32:14,216 --> 00:32:16,389
Currently,
the Democratic Republican Party...

395
00:32:16,472 --> 00:32:17,558
Mr. Jung.

396
00:32:19,347 --> 00:32:21,374
What should we do with Min Jun-won?

397
00:32:23,978 --> 00:32:25,371
Don't mind him.

398
00:32:27,459 --> 00:32:29,361
Should I dig about his son?

399
00:32:34,925 --> 00:32:37,225
Is that necessary?

400
00:32:38,996 --> 00:32:42,328
We need something on him
since he's bothering us.

401
00:32:44,238 --> 00:32:45,222
Okay.

402
00:32:53,786 --> 00:32:54,878
Professor Lee.

403
00:32:58,956 --> 00:33:00,061
Professor Lee.

404
00:33:04,697 --> 00:33:07,219
I have something to ask you.

405
00:33:10,384 --> 00:33:13,654
My kid is getting a surgery tomorrow.

406
00:33:13,737 --> 00:33:18,805
I wonder if I could have tomorrow
and the day after off.

407
00:33:18,888 --> 00:33:21,550
It's nothing serious,

408
00:33:21,633 --> 00:33:24,621
but my kid is still in middle school,
so...

409
00:33:26,025 --> 00:33:27,443
Why is...

410
00:33:29,794 --> 00:33:31,482
everyone doing this to me?

411
00:33:43,593 --> 00:33:45,652
You can't do this all of a sudden.

412
00:33:48,090 --> 00:33:52,517
Don't you know that the campaign team
is having a meal here tomorrow?

413
00:33:57,283 --> 00:33:59,076
Why are you so selfish?

414
00:33:59,945 --> 00:34:02,383
Please don't worry about that.

415
00:34:02,466 --> 00:34:04,463
I already prepared everything,

416
00:34:04,546 --> 00:34:06,333
and someone else will come instead.

417
00:34:10,067 --> 00:34:11,767
Someone I don't know is coming?

418
00:34:11,850 --> 00:34:14,151
No, no. It's not a stranger.

419
00:34:14,234 --> 00:34:16,566
It's Yang Soo-jin.

420
00:34:16,649 --> 00:34:20,742
She came several times before
whenever we had big events.

421
00:34:20,825 --> 00:34:24,944
You know, the tall girl with short hair.

422
00:34:25,660 --> 00:34:28,130
You'll recognize her when you see her.

423
00:34:39,116 --> 00:34:40,328
I see.

424
00:34:41,133 --> 00:34:45,180
Now that I think about it,
it might inconvenience you.

425
00:34:47,278 --> 00:34:48,931
I'm sorry,

426
00:34:49,014 --> 00:34:51,836
please don't mind me. It's okay.

427
00:34:51,919 --> 00:34:53,561
How can I act like nothing happened?

428
00:34:57,821 --> 00:35:00,444
Why are you making me
look like a bad person?

429
00:35:01,754 --> 00:35:03,611
Are you going to cancel the surgery?

430
00:35:05,600 --> 00:35:08,039
No, it's not like that...

431
00:35:08,122 --> 00:35:10,017
Why do I have to

432
00:35:10,100 --> 00:35:12,145
humor you too?

433
00:35:12,716 --> 00:35:15,497
Why do I have to pay attention
to such things?

434
00:35:40,269 --> 00:35:41,382
It's fine.

435
00:35:42,876 --> 00:35:44,134
Just take two days off.

436
00:35:47,165 --> 00:35:49,269
I'm sorry, Professor Lee.

437
00:35:49,352 --> 00:35:52,237
I asked you too last minute.

438
00:35:53,952 --> 00:35:58,697
It can't be helped in your situation.

439
00:36:00,173 --> 00:36:03,859
Sorry I'm a little sensitive today.

440
00:36:05,438 --> 00:36:07,404
We'll eat out tomorrow.

441
00:36:12,439 --> 00:36:13,585
What is it?

442
00:36:16,118 --> 00:36:18,081
I came to get you for the dinner.

443
00:36:22,494 --> 00:36:26,706
From now on, call me from downstairs.

444
00:36:27,823 --> 00:36:28,787
Yes, Ma'am.

445
00:36:29,416 --> 00:36:34,637
She usually never yells.

446
00:36:36,159 --> 00:36:39,073
It's because I made a mistake today.

447
00:36:53,311 --> 00:36:58,017
Ms. Cho. You must be someone honest.

448
00:36:58,734 --> 00:37:02,279
No, I'm just someone ordinary.

449
00:37:02,362 --> 00:37:06,530
Isn't it hard working for Ji-hoon?

450
00:37:07,910 --> 00:37:09,137
Not at all.

451
00:37:10,086 --> 00:37:12,801
I know this job
doesn't allow any time off.

452
00:37:14,509 --> 00:37:17,139
But it's a precious opportunity for me,

453
00:37:17,222 --> 00:37:19,608
so I want to do my best
and get recognized.

454
00:37:24,468 --> 00:37:27,808
Also, he's very nice to me.

455
00:37:29,940 --> 00:37:31,022
See?

456
00:37:34,459 --> 00:37:36,320
Everyone lies.

457
00:37:37,214 --> 00:37:40,332
No, I'm telling you the truth.

458
00:37:50,856 --> 00:37:53,737
Ma'am, he's asking you to wait 20 minutes.

459
00:37:55,103 --> 00:37:56,037
Why?

460
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:58,657
He says you should come in
after everyone arrives.

461
00:37:59,694 --> 00:38:01,467
I'll go in and check first.

462
00:38:25,694 --> 00:38:27,677
I don't think he's here yet.

463
00:38:27,760 --> 00:38:28,661
What?

464
00:38:28,744 --> 00:38:31,251
I checked
with the restaurant manager twice.

465
00:38:31,334 --> 00:38:33,816
What a joke.

466
00:38:36,144 --> 00:38:38,089
It'd be ridiculous to wait here.

467
00:38:38,172 --> 00:38:39,431
Let's circle around.

468
00:38:40,133 --> 00:38:41,063
Yes, Ma'am.

469
00:38:48,392 --> 00:38:49,956
Hey, Mom.

470
00:38:50,039 --> 00:38:52,081
Can I skip this meeting?

471
00:38:54,212 --> 00:38:58,064
I think he's crazy.
That stupid doctor isn't here yet.

472
00:39:15,061 --> 00:39:17,144
Let's go in. Everyone's here.

473
00:39:20,133 --> 00:39:22,532
It's not like everything always goes
the way you want.

474
00:39:23,273 --> 00:39:24,689
No, of course not.

475
00:39:24,772 --> 00:39:28,064
It's the will of the people
and the will of the party.

476
00:39:30,015 --> 00:39:32,123
But if the will

477
00:39:32,206 --> 00:39:35,924
keeps on changing,

478
00:39:36,007 --> 00:39:39,027
the people will get confused.

479
00:39:40,375 --> 00:39:42,627
Things change by the day.

480
00:39:42,710 --> 00:39:44,843
I don't know what to tell you.

481
00:39:44,926 --> 00:39:46,269
It's okay.

482
00:39:46,352 --> 00:39:49,574
You were elected four times
and you'll act as my pacemaker,

483
00:39:49,657 --> 00:39:50,984
so I'm happy.

484
00:39:53,480 --> 00:39:56,866
You say it's urgent,
so could you tell me what it's about?

485
00:39:57,714 --> 00:39:58,704
Here.

486
00:40:02,895 --> 00:40:03,838
-Please have a drink.
-Okay.

487
00:40:03,921 --> 00:40:04,935
Sir.

488
00:40:06,747 --> 00:40:07,837
Thank you.

489
00:40:07,920 --> 00:40:09,663
It's been so long since we drank.

490
00:41:04,189 --> 00:41:06,388
LEE ANNA

491
00:41:13,174 --> 00:41:14,710
LEE ANNA, PROFESSOR

492
00:41:14,793 --> 00:41:16,393
YALE UNIVERSITY,
MASTER OF EAST ASIAN STUDIES

493
00:41:24,600 --> 00:41:25,587
Jae-ho.

494
00:41:26,688 --> 00:41:29,455
Why didn't you call me in advance?
Do you want some coffee?

495
00:41:29,538 --> 00:41:32,015
No, it's okay.
I stopped by on my way to the airport.

496
00:41:32,098 --> 00:41:33,661
-Are you going to the US?
-Yes.

497
00:41:35,710 --> 00:41:38,856
By the way, you changed companies.

498
00:41:39,446 --> 00:41:40,354
Right.

499
00:41:45,815 --> 00:41:46,867
"Bokuk"?

500
00:41:48,006 --> 00:41:49,467
Isn't it the biggest one in Korea?

501
00:41:49,550 --> 00:41:50,816
Yes.

502
00:41:51,612 --> 00:41:54,680
I didn't make the cut
when I took the entrance exam before,

503
00:41:54,763 --> 00:41:56,349
but I'll work hard from now.

504
00:41:57,027 --> 00:41:59,127
The elections are soon, so it's hectic.

505
00:41:59,843 --> 00:42:02,504
Good for you. I think you'll do well.

506
00:42:02,587 --> 00:42:03,660
Thank you.

507
00:42:05,025 --> 00:42:06,886
By the way,

508
00:42:06,969 --> 00:42:10,659
I don't think you would have came here
just to see me.

509
00:42:18,183 --> 00:42:19,312
Is this

510
00:42:21,339 --> 00:42:22,495
Lee Yu-mi?

511
00:42:24,443 --> 00:42:25,400
Yes.

512
00:42:26,285 --> 00:42:28,950
I didn't want things to be awkward,
so I never brought her up.

513
00:42:32,204 --> 00:42:35,232
I'm not going to live in Korea anyway,

514
00:42:35,315 --> 00:42:37,279
so it doesn't matter what she does.

515
00:42:39,044 --> 00:42:42,594
But I thought I should tell you
why I broke up with her.

516
00:42:42,677 --> 00:42:45,465
Jae-ho, let bygones be bygones.

517
00:42:45,548 --> 00:42:46,957
It's not that, Ji-won.

518
00:42:50,915 --> 00:42:52,399
Lee Yu-mi

519
00:42:54,643 --> 00:42:55,905
didn't go to your school.

520
00:42:59,116 --> 00:43:00,087
What?

521
00:43:00,941 --> 00:43:03,338
I have no idea how she graduated
from NYU and Yale

522
00:43:03,421 --> 00:43:05,471
to become a professor,

523
00:43:07,691 --> 00:43:09,486
but she was a fake university student
when we were dating.

524
00:43:10,821 --> 00:43:12,230
She was preparing for her SATs
a third time.

